{"event_type": "planner.agent_message", "event_version": "0.0", "raw_event": {"event_type": "codex.raw.agent_message", "event_version": "0.0", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_210", "text": "Implemented the finalize-stage finish line in [`FinalizeStage.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/FinalizeStage.tsx): it now has tabbed `Read story` / `Listen back` surfaces, a compact completion summary panel, durable story-asset loading with accepted-manuscript fallback, inline audio review with partial/failure states, and the existing revision-compare tools preserved below. I also added `fetchSessionAssetText(...)` in [`sessionArtifacts.ts`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionArtifacts.ts), expanded finalize coverage in [`FinalizeStage.test.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/FinalizeStage.test.tsx), and updated [`index.css`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/styles/index.css) for the new layout plus a browser-found stacking fix that kept the sticky review panel from blocking tab clicks.\n\nVerification completed on the final code state: `npx vitest run src/features/session/FinalizeStage.test.tsx`, full `npm test` (`22` files / `116` tests), `npm run lint`, and `npm run build` all passed. Docker-backed visual QA was blocked because the Docker daemon never became reachable, so I used a local Vite + Playwright fallback with mocked hydration/story responses; that produced passing browser checks and screenshots at `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-read-desktop.png`, `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-listen-desktop.png`, and `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-listen-mobile.png`. I wrote the required reviewer summary to [`summary.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/80_finalize_screen_with_read_and_listen_modes/summary.md). Commits created: `28197fa` and `91bf5f6`.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "run_id": "852e59ae-7e3c-580a-9c17-7f38e0f42b62", "timestamp": "2026-04-02T20:19:54.279240-07:00"}, "run_id": "852e59ae-7e3c-580a-9c17-7f38e0f42b62", "text": "Implemented the finalize-stage finish line in [`FinalizeStage.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/FinalizeStage.tsx): it now has tabbed `Read story` / `Listen back` surfaces, a compact completion summary panel, durable story-asset loading with accepted-manuscript fallback, inline audio review with partial/failure states, and the existing revision-compare tools preserved below. I also added `fetchSessionAssetText(...)` in [`sessionArtifacts.ts`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionArtifacts.ts), expanded finalize coverage in [`FinalizeStage.test.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/FinalizeStage.test.tsx), and updated [`index.css`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/styles/index.css) for the new layout plus a browser-found stacking fix that kept the sticky review panel from blocking tab clicks.\n\nVerification completed on the final code state: `npx vitest run src/features/session/FinalizeStage.test.tsx`, full `npm test` (`22` files / `116` tests), `npm run lint`, and `npm run build` all passed. Docker-backed visual QA was blocked because the Docker daemon never became reachable, so I used a local Vite + Playwright fallback with mocked hydration/story responses; that produced passing browser checks and screenshots at `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-read-desktop.png`, `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-listen-desktop.png`, and `/tmp/storyteller-finalize-listen-mobile.png`. I wrote the required reviewer summary to [`summary.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/80_finalize_screen_with_read_and_listen_modes/summary.md). Commits created: `28197fa` and `91bf5f6`.", "timestamp": "2026-04-02T20:19:54.279240-07:00"}
